                    "company": "Proyecto Arqueol\u00f3gico Centro de Nicaragua (PACEN)",
                    "description": "I supervised a team of  4 students and a local guide during a systematic clay survey of my own design throughout a 52 sq km area. This clay survey represented the first  component of the extensive research I performed on clay sources related to pottery-making practices, which also included ethnographic studies and archaeological excavations. Additionally, I studied the geological material collected in the field together with ceramic materials obtained from archaeological sites of the area. Both mineral resources as well as archaeological objects were analysed using macro-fabric analysis, thin section petrography, pXRF and WDXRF. The results of my research provided the first evidence for clay procurement practices in the Chontales region of pre-Hispanic Nicaragua, and built the only systematic compositional reference collection for clays in the whole country.",
